Motive and intro to the project

¶

As we can see the global inflation and the local inflation in Egypt, and also there was a ***problem in importing goods due to the last decisions that were made by Central Bank Egypt***

 

I saw a necessary urge to investigate the dynamic of prices in Cheese as it is used nearly in every home in Egypt and also with kids in schools.
I collected data from famous retailer across more than one month and did some insights to get a glimpse of view about cheese market in Egypt lately

 

N.B Data was collected from 20-9-2022 to 3-11-2022

 

I will focus on some brands due to its popularity according to the main stream of society and I will neglect the premium ones the brands that i will focus on is
  • La vache qui rit
  • Kiri
  • Domty
  • President

</ul>

plotting histogram of prices to see the distribution of prices¶

In [291]:
plt.hist(df_tot['RealPrices']);
plt.title('Distribution of cheese prices');

we see that the histogram is right skewed which is expected as we talk about cheese which is supposed that many Products and items has a relative lower price compared to other products , we see that the majority contain prices lower than 200

Is the mean of cheese prices is a real indicator for the cheese ?¶

In [292]:
df_tot['RealPrices'].mean()
Out[292]:
160.50508300062276

the answer is no, as the mean will be affected by the premium products that are there which will push to to be a higher mean a better indicator is to use the median as a measure of average

In [293]:
df_tot['RealPrices'].median()
Out[293]:
89.95

as expected, the median gives a lower number compared to the mean which was a little deceving measure of average

Getting the most date where the max prices happened¶

In [295]:
plt.scatter(products_max['RealPrices'],products_max['Date'])
plt.xticks(rotation=90);
plt.title('Dates where max price happened');

we find that the date where most of the SKUS reached its maximum price was 9-10-2022 ¶

 

That is because this date was near two holidays which was sixth october victory and birth of prophet muhammed

Q4 how does the mean of prices of cheese market behaves ?¶

one can think that the mean of the prices was decreasing in certain days like the beginning of the plot, but that wasn't due to the prices but due to that some SKUS weren't available but in the tail of the plot we can see that the mean is increasing and at this period SKUS count was constant so that change was due to real increase in prices
